'''Irol''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] native of an [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Unidentified Outer Rim forest planet|forest planet]], where he learned how to fly a [[Speeder bike/Legends|speeder bike]]. By [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], he had become a [[Scout trooper/Legends|scout trooper]] [[Sergeant/Legends|sergeant]] in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], and was part of the [[Garrison/Legends|garrison]] stationed on the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]], whose assignment was to defend the [[Endor shield generator bunker|shield generator bunker]] protecting the [[Orbit/Legends|orbiting]] [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]]. That [[Standard year/Legends|year]], Irol took part in the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], where he and the rest of the garrison unsuccessfully attempted to defend the [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|shield generator]] from a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[Endor strike team/Legends|strike team]].

==Biography==
The [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="CVD" /> [[Gender/Legends|male]]<ref name="SE" /> Irol<ref name="CCG" /> was a [[Cloning/Legends|clone]]<ref name="TCG" /> who hailed from a [[Unidentified Outer Rim forest planet|forest planet]] located in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]].<ref name="CCG" /> It was on that [[Planet/Legends|planet]] where<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|115|Irol, Sergeant}}</ref> he<ref name="CCG" /> learned how to fly a [[Speeder bike/Legends|speeder bike]].<ref name="CSWE" /> By the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]] to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> Irol joined the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] as a [[Scout trooper/Legends|scout trooper]], and attained the [[Military rank/Legends|military rank]] of [[Sergeant/Legends|sergeant]].<ref name="CCG" /> He became a member of the Imperial [[Garrison/Legends|garrison]] stationed on the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]],<ref name="CSWE" /> whose assignment was to protect the [[Endor shield generator bunker|shield generator bunker]] for the [[Orbit/Legends|orbiting]] Imperial [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]].<ref name="RotJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref> In 4 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]],<ref name="NEC" /> Irol and the garrison took part in the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]],<ref name="CCG" /> during which a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[Endor strike team/Legends|strike team]] infiltrated the [[Tree/Legends|forest]] [[Moon/Legends|moon]] with the intention to destroy the [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|shield generator]]. The battle ended with the Alliance successfully destroying the shield generator, allowing the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] to destroy the unprotected [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]] in [[Realspace/Legends|space]].<ref name="RotJ" />

==Personality and traits==
A confident biker [[Scout/Legends|scout]] and hunter, Irol relied on superior balance and strength to operate his [[74-Z speeder bike/Legends|74-Z speeder bike]].<ref name="CCG" /> Irol's balance and flying skills made him a valuable, though cocky, member of the Imperial garrison on Endor.<ref name="CSWE" />

==Equipment==
Irol wore a full suit of [[Scout trooper armor/Legends|scout trooper armor]] and wielded a [[Scout trooper blaster pistol/Legends|scout trooper blaster pistol]].<ref name="Kenner toy">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (toy line)|pack=Biker Scout|link=vintbikerscout.asp}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Originally pictured in an onset photo<ref name="Topps">{{Topps|set=1983 Topps Star Wars: Return of the Jedi Series 1|cardname=Biker Scout and the Battlefield|link=https://www.tcdb.com/ViewCard.cfm/sid/72969/cid/5256947/1983-Topps-Return-Of-The-Jedi-97-Biker-Scout-and-the-Battlefield}}</ref> for the [[1983]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']],<ref name="RotJ" /> Irol was first brought into the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity that year by [[Topps]] Collectibles for their ''[[1983 Topps Star Wars: Return of the Jedi Series 1]]'' set.<ref name="Topps" /> A picture of the scout trooper was used in [[May]] [[1994]]'s short story "[[Whispers in the Dark]]," written by [[Charlene Newcomb]] for [[West End Games]]' [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 2|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 2]], thus marking Irol's first [[in-universe]] appearance.<ref name="whispers">{{JournalCite|2|Whispers in the Dark}}</ref> In [[1999]], he was first identified by name on a card for the ''[[Endor Limited]]'' set of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]],<ref name="CCG" /> with the name simultaneously being used in the gameplay statistic text for another character, [[Corporal/Legends|Corporal]] [[Drelosyn]].<ref name="Drelosyn">{{CCG|set=Endor Limited|cardname=Corporal Drelosyn}}</ref>

